            <section id="correlation-coefficient" class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-[#004AAD] mb-4 text-center">The Correlation Coefficient (r)</h2>
                <p class="text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-6">The first step in analyzing a linear relationship is to measure its strength and direction. The Product Moment Linear Correlation Coefficient, or 'r', is a single value that tells us exactly this. It always falls between -1 and +1.</p>
                <div class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto">
                    <div class="relative w-full h-4 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#004AAD] via-gray-200 to-[#004AAD] rounded-full">
                        <div class="absolute top-1/2 left-0 w-5 h-5 bg-[#004AAD] rounded-full -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2"></div>
                        <div class="absolute top-1/2 left-1/2 w-5 h-5 bg-gray-500 rounded-full -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2"></div>
                        <div class="absolute top-1/2 left-full w-5 h-5 bg-[#004AAD] rounded-full -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2"></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="relative flex justify-between w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-2 text-sm font-semibold">
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <p class="text-[#004AAD]">-1.0</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-600">Perfect Negative</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="text-center">
                            <p class="text-gray-600">0.0</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-600">No Correlation</p>
