            <section id="scatter-plots" class="mb-12">
                <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-[#004AAD] mb-4 text-center">Visualizing Correlation with Scatter Plots</h2>
                <p class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">The best way to understand correlation is to see it. A scatter plot graphs pairs of data points to reveal the underlying relationship between two variables. The pattern of the dots tells the story of their connection.</p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                    
                    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
                        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-center mb-2 text-[#0079FF]">Strong Positive Correlation (r â‰ˆ 0.9)</h3>
                        <p class="text-sm text-center text-gray-600 mb-4">As one variable increases, the other variable also tends to increase. The points cluster tightly around an upward-sloping line.</p>
                        <div class="chart-container">
                            <canvas id="positiveCorrelationChart"></canvas>
                        </div>
                    </div>

